This time round, competitors will only racce through the route on June 21 and 22 driving ordinary cars, unlike in the past when factory teams spent months of testing in preparation for the Safari while taking their own notes.Bhabra and company have spent back-breaking months of preparing notes and maps to help guide competitors through the sections. We took a four-day expedition on the entire route of the 2021 World Rally Championship Safari Rally last week, a harrowing experience in some sections and exhilarating invitation of speed on others.
The final verdict? The Safari will be a hell-for-rubber excursion for the cars! Though short by over 4,000 kilometres, compared to events of 27 years ago, the Safari still retains the iconic toughness.



