The route is compact but a true test for drivers alertness and reliability of cars which will need to be driven flat out without costly errors for one to finish.
The Kedong Ranch, Hells Gate, Malewa and Loldia section within a 40km radius in areas surrounding Naivasha is a journey to the unknown; Soysambu Conservancy, neighbouring Sleeping Warrior and Elmentaita routes in Gilgil are unpredictable.
The jewel of them all remains the designated Loldia “shakedown” 5km loop, 30km down Moi South road from Naivasha town. It is the complete postcard of breathtaking geographical features. It consists of plains intertwined with forested rocky patches teeming with wildlife.





It is home to buffaloes, Zebra, Giraffes and an extended family of deer, Magical Kenya images which the Safari of yore never captured on TV consistently.
This is the destination any fan loving Kenyan should venture into on the morning of June 23 next year with day-long action galore.
Loldia will offer top drivers the opportunity to drive in rally speeds to test their machines and prepare for a rigorous four days in front of the media and spectators before rally proper zooms off outside the Kenyatta International Convention Centre on June 24, followed by side-by-side start of the Safari at the Super Special stage behind Kasarani Stadium.



