This will please the eyes of the fans and fire their imagination in a mouth-watering spectacle as a precursor of the high-octane rally weekend.





Whereas there is no comparison between drivers in the top WRC cars and our local ones, it will be interesting to see, as it was in the beginning, whether local knowledge will prove a major advantage for the later who will sample parts of the route in the Arc Equator Rally next April before the Safari.
This time round, competitors will only racce through the route on June 21 and 22 driving ordinary cars, unlike in the past when factory teams spent months of testing in preparation for the Safari while taking their own notes.
Bhabra and company have spent back-breaking months of preparing notes and maps to help guide competitors through the sections.
